The paper presents new algorithms for solving L1 regularized classification problems with Renyi differential privacy. This topic is closely related to machine learning and privacy, which are covered by several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on developing new algorithms for classification problems. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely, as the paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category, as the paper discusses optimization problems. cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are less likely but still possible, as they are related to privacy and machine learning.
